history.text: Hello. How are you?
Are you a Zootopia fan?
I am good. I have never seen the movie. Have you every heard of anthropomorphic mammals?
I have not actually
Juddy Hopps fulfills her childhood dream of becoming a police officer. Do you feel that this inspires people to dream?
I think it does actually.
Did you see the 98 rating on Rotten Tomatoes? That is really good
Do you feel that Judy, the rabbit, is a good animal to choose for the role? In the movie she seems to doubt her potential. No, I did not see it.
I think it is a great choice.
Unfortunately, she is fooled by a con artist fox. Do you feel there are real life foxes who steal others dream as portrayed in the movie?
I do not think so. The movie had two directors. That is interesting.
Unfortunately, Judy was class valedictorian but was on parking duty. Do you feel that this goes against the stereotype that valedictorians will have success later in life?
I am not sure. The message of the film is really nice.
How do you feel about Judy changing into a criminal or blackmailing Nick?
I think that was a good thing because it allowed her to grow from that and change later
Do you like that a bad deed by Judy turned into a mission that would save Nick?
I thought that was really interesting
There are people who are bullied in real life. Do you feel that having a fox or Nick being portrayed as a person being bullied is a good animal to choose for this role?
Yeah, a fox is a good choice in my view
In society, the city would never allow access to traffic cameras. Do you feel that city hall was correct in allowing this access to Judy and Nick?
Yes, I think so. Did you see the rating on iIMDB was 8/10?
I think that is a good rating for an animated film. However, there is an important detail in the story. Do you feel that Judy should have quit her job?
I think so. I don't see any other way for everything working out
Do you suppose that receiving praise for good deeds can sometimes lead to one's demise?
Of course. It can give one a lot of ego.
I think so too. I feel that Judy made the right decision.
I agree.
There were many great lessons in Zootopia.
Thats what makes it so great
did you like the sloth?
No, it seems as if the interesting character is Judy. She goes through many challenges that test her dreams and ambitions and learns some important lessons about friendship and the law.
Thanks for chatting!
Thanks
